verses.verse: Praise<WH1984> you the Lord<WH3050>. Praise<WH1984>, O you servants<WH5650> of the Lord<WH3068>, praise<WH1984> the name<WH8034> of the Lord<WH3068>.
Blessed<WH1288> be the name<WH8034> of the Lord<WH3068> from this time forth<WH6258> and for<WH5704> evermore<WH5769>.
From the rising<WH4217> of the sun<WH8121> unto the going down<WH3996> of the same the Lord<WH3068>'s name<WH8034> is to be praised<WH1984>.
The Lord<WH3068> is high<WH7311> above all nations<WH1471>, and his glory<WH3519> above the heavens<WH8064>.
Who is like unto the Lord<WH3068> our God<WH430>, who dwells<WH3427> on high<WH1361>,
Who humbles<WH8213> himself to behold<WH7200> the things that are in heaven<WH8064>, and in the earth<WH776>!
He raises up<WH6965> the poor<WH1800> out of the dust<WH6083>, and lifts<WH7311> the needy<WH34> out of the dunghill<WH830>;
That he may set<WH3427> him with princes<WH5081>, even with the princes<WH5081> of his people<WH5971>.
He makes the childless woman<WH6135> to keep<WH3427> house<WH1004>, and to be a joyful<WH8056> mother<WH517> of sons<WH1121>. Praise<WH1984> you the Lord<WH3050>.
